# Tests

This Power-Up ships a Node.js test suite (built-in `node:test` runner, no Jest/Vitest).

## Commands

```bash
npm test              # unit + sandbox verify integration tests
npm run test:unit     # unit tests only (faster)
npm run test:coverage # unit tests with V8 coverage for components/
npm run verify        # legacy sandbox verifies (includes Windows cscript presets)
```

Requires **Node.js 18+** on `PATH`. Under the hood, `scripts/run-tests.js` invokes `node --test`.

## When to run

After changing logic under `components/` (scoring, matrix, statut, completion, effects, agent, version), run `npm test` (or at least `npm run test:unit`) before considering the task done. If coverage drops on the file you touched, add or extend a test under `test/`.

## Layout

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `test/*.test.js` | Unit tests — `require()` production IIFEs via `test/helpers/load.js` |
| `test/sandbox-verifies.test.js` | Spawns existing `sandbox/verify-*.js` scripts |
| `sandbox/verify-*.js` | Standalone verifies (still runnable directly) |

Do not load production scripts with `vm.runInNewContext` in new unit tests — use `loadComponent()` so coverage instrumentation works.

Three sandbox verifies are currently skipped as known-failing (`verify-completion.js`, `verify-card-dream.js`, `verify-progress-complete.js`). Prefer fixing those scripts or the product code over re-enabling them while red.
